X
Y
(Z,d)
d(X,Y):=\inf \{d(x,y): x\in X, y\in Y\}
x_0\in X
y_0\in Y
d(x_0,y_0)=d(X,Y)
X \times Y
d \colon X \times Y \to \mathbf{R}
x_n \in X, y_n \in Y
d(x_n,y_n) \to d(X,Y)
X,Y
x \in X, y \in Y
x_{n_k} \to x, y_{n_k} \to y
d(x,y) \le d(x,x_{n_k}) + d(x_{n_k}, y_{n_k}) + d( y_{n_k}, y)
d(x,y) \le \lim_{k \to \infty} d(x_{n_k}, y_{n_k}) = d(X,Y)
